subsection.def:
locked
                    (鎖上) means secured by a device which prevents
                unauthorized operation;

subparagraph.content:
that whilst it may be very convenient to keep the door open for
                            prolonged periods such an arrangement could put the safety of the ship
                            at risk if the hull were suddenly breached;

the increased risk of personnel being trapped by doors which do not
                            have the improved facilities for local operation described in
                                paragraph 2(1) of Schedule 1;
